# Content CMS

Blog content lives in `content/posts/` as Markdown files. No database or admin UI — agents and editors work directly with files.

## Post Schema

Each file: `content/posts/{slug}.md`

```yaml
---
title: "Post Title"
date: "2026-01-15"
description: "Optional summary for listings and SEO."
---
```

| Field | Required | Notes |
|-------|----------|-------|
| `title` | yes | Display heading |
| `date` | yes | ISO date string (`YYYY-MM-DD`), sorted newest first |
| `description` | no | Shown on `/writing` index and in metadata |

**Slug** = filename without `.md`. URL: `/writing/{slug}`.

## Pipeline

1. `gray-matter` parses frontmatter
2. `remark` + `remark-html` converts body to HTML
3. Rendered via `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` with `prose prose-neutral` classes

## Auto-Discovery

New posts appear automatically on:

- Home page (latest 3)
- `/writing` index
- `/writing/[slug]` (via `generateStaticParams`)
- `sitemap.xml`

No registry file to update.

## Writing Style

- Plain Markdown in the body
- No emojis in titles or body text
- Keep frontmatter values in double quotes
